      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nThis patch reverses the logic of the LASSERTF() when converting it into a check, and this causes all kinds of test failures later in the code:\n\n 05:58:56:LustreError: 8765:0:(lod_lov.c:844:lod_load_striping()) ASSERTION( lo->ldo_stripenr == 0 ) failed: \n 05:58:56:LustreError: 8765:0:(lod_lov.c:844:lod_load_striping()) LBUG\n 05:58:56:Pid: 8765, comm: mdt00_004\n 05:58:56:\n 05:58:56:Call Trace:\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa05d5895>] libcfs_debug_dumpstack+0x55/0x80 [libcfs]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa05d5e97>] lbug_with_loc+0x47/0xb0 [libcfs]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0fe50d3>] lod_load_striping+0x383/0x4b0 [lod]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0fefe4b>] lod_declare_object_destroy+0x16b/0x390 [lod]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0ec7250>] mdd_declare_finish_unlink+0x90/0x170 [mdd]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0eccfaa>] mdd_unlink+0x3ca/0xe30 [mdd]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f364e8>] mdo_unlink+0x18/0x50 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f399c0>] mdt_reint_unlink+0x820/0x1010 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f361e1>] mdt_reint_rec+0x41/0xe0 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f1d563>] mdt_reint_internal+0x4c3/0x780 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f1d864>] mdt_reint+0x44/0xe0 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f2054a>] mdt_handle_common+0x52a/0x1460 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa0f5a925>] mds_regular_handle+0x15/0x20 [mdt]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa08ea018>] ptlrpc_server_handle_request+0x398/0xc60 [ptlrpc]\n 05:58:56: [<ffffffffa08eb39d>] ptlrpc_main+0xabd/0x1700 [ptlrpc]\n\nObviously this patch needs to be fixed, but the LASSERT() in lod_load_striping() needs to be fixed as well, since if this patched code ever returns an error it would just fail slightly later on.  It doesn't make sense that lod_load_striping() should LASSERT() on layout contents anyway, since they may be corrupted on disk.  At worst it should return an error and the file is inaccessible.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
